      },
      {
        "step_no": 2,
        "text": "Portion mixture into even meatballs (about 60 g / 2 oz each) using a scoop or hands and place on a tray; refrigerate for 5 minutes to help them hold shape.",
        "time_min": 7
      },
      {
        "step_no": 3,
        "text": "Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat until shimmering; add meatballs in a single layer without crowding and sear, turning occasionally, until golden on most sides (about 8 minutes total). Work in batches if needed.",
        "time_min": 8
      },
      {
        "step_no": 4,
        "text": "Remove excess oil, then add cherry tomatoes to the skillet and cook until they begin to burst; deglaze with chicken broth or water, scraping up browned bits.",
        "time_min": 4
      },
      {
        "step_no": 5,
        "text": "Return meatballs to the pan, add olives if using, lemon zest and juice, and reduce heat to medium-low; simmer gently, uncovered, until meatballs are cooked through (internal temp 74°C/165°F) and sauce thickens slightly.",
        "time_min": 7
      },
      {
        "step_no": 6,
        "text": "While meatballs simmer, quickly sauté spiralized zucchini in a separate skillet with a small drizzle of olive oil for 1–2 minutes to warm and slightly soften, then season lightly.",
        "time_min": 3
      },
      {
        "step_no": 7,
        "text": "Finish by tasting and adjusting seasoning, sprinkle extra chopped parsley and optional red pepper flakes, then serve meatballs and sauce over zucchini noodles or a salad.",
